               <desc type="building-data" xml:lang="en">
                  <p source="#bibl000048sa-1"> Also known as the <placeName ref="/place/000048ta">Emerald Wave Bridge (碧瀾橋)</placeName>. 
                     The original date of construction is unknown. 
                     A bridge appears in this location on Gao Ruxing's 高汝行 plan of the site published in 1551,
                     and may have been built at the same time as the Taishan Temple, that is, prior to 1342. 
                     It is labeled Taishan Bridge on the Qianlong period (1736-1795) painting of the site.
                     The bridge is number 28 on the<placeName ref="/place/000048">Jin Shrines</placeName>
                     site plan.</p>
               </desc>
